      "content": "I can see why you'd think that, but disappearing isn't the answer. Your kids need you, even if they don't always show it. They're still learning and growing, and they need your guidance, even if it's imperfect. It's not about \"ruining\" their childhood, it's about being present and trying your best. And as for being a \"poison\" - that's just not true. You're their parent, and they love you, even if they don't always show it.",
